<br>
As an enchanter, you should know this.....   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ommundan>Ommundan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.datecc.de/bilder/woag/bilder/misc/misc59d.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of The Hunt</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#333333>(1/16/03 12:24:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1779.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.cfl.rr.com/exarch/files/PAINT1.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A couple quick questions</span><hr size=1> Lets get the Hijack crap out of the way first...<br>
<br>
A <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>BOT</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> is an automated character (think roBOT). He was takin' offense to you implying so and responding in a role playing fashion (saying his caracter would beat you up, not him personaly). Bot'ing is illegal by the eula as it requires other &quot;tools&quot; to automate other characters. Now if you're talking about having hotkeys set up to run multiple characters efficiently, that's called many different things like &quot;two (or three or whatever) boxing&quot; but I've never heard of a character being ran by a person as a BOT.<br>
<br>
And so far through this flame infested thread more hostility has come from everyone else that it has from the origional poster.<br>
<br>
You don't like the concept of powerleveling? Then how about doing us a favor and go post your own thread about the evils of the PL and not hijack a thread to go on a players morals crusade.<br>
<br>
Skills are easy to raise afterwards (I forgot to train meditate and channeling and to specialize with my druid and she was 34 before I really noticed it (playing her normally and noticed how she didnt perform as well as my mage).<br>
<br>
As for player skills, maybe he just wants a CoTH character? As long as he doesnt try to pass himself off as a great mage to an unknowing group I see no problems with him leveling up fast and then learn the skills as time permits.<br>
<br>
-----------<br>
<br>
Now advice to the poster...<br>
<br>
<br>
With an enchanter and cleric, the mem blur route would probably be the quickest way to get the mage into the 40's. Then switch to normal &quot;group&quot; tactics using mage pet as the tank (while you're not grouped of course) to get as far into the 50's as you want.<br>
<br>
The biggest problems with powerleveling are:<br>
<br>
Players - They get annoyed at you killing everything so you want to find an out of the way place. They also get jealous and bug the crap out of you (another reason to find an out of the way place) and I suppose on PVP th &quot;bugging&quot; could be a real pain in the butt.<br>
<br>
Skills - Your casting skills take a while to go up. Keep the characters Int as high as possible as it helps the skill learning. Also since you 2 or 3 box it would be easy to have the mage sitting somewhere casting lvl 1 spells on himself to raise skills. You could even make a hotkey with pauses so that you could cast three spells off one button push.<br>
<br>
Good luck =)<br>
