<br>
In most games I'd agree with your definition. Boting would normally be a computer controlled character. However, in EQ (and a lot of things) a new set of definitions arise due to common usage. Since I'm not aware of any commonly used software that allows an automated PC in EQ, but the term still gets used often in EQ I'd say that isn't what the common EQ definition is. <br>
<br>
By common usage I'd say that botting in considered to be a character played on a second (or third or what have you) computer used in limited capacity (ie buff-bot, port-bot, heal-bot, CoH-bot, etc). The key is that a second character or more isn't played with the same ability that a character that has someone's full controll and so you use only a fraction of it's core abilities (even malkar seems to think this is true, but he applies it only to one class &quot;botting is having a cleric or something for raids when you need more on the ch cycle. &quot;).  Typical bots are pleveled characters that the player never intends to play the tradional way (as in one character one computer, give the character your full attention and learn to play as well as you can). Given what I believe is the common usage it's easy to see that Malkar wants to bot a mage. <br>
<br>
Lastly, as to the flaming. Let me quote Malkar's entire post in question here: &quot;botting is having a cleric or something for raids when you need more on the ch cycle. Both my lvl 65's are my main characters I don't do anythign without both. Malkaz would bitch slap your mangy ass if you called him a bot to his face. &quot; Sorry, the post taken as whole is NOT in character. Perhaps the action of &quot;bitch slap&quot; might be in character, but it's the person making the post using the insult &quot;mangy ass&quot; and Mantria as a common poster to this forum deserves more respect than that. Dig around a bit. Malkar's posts so far in Magician's Tower have been generally disrespectful in tone, and I'm usually one of the last people to call someone on it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showMessageRange?topicID=1779.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showMessageRange?topicID=1779.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showPrevMessage?topicID=1779.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showNextMessage?topicID=1779.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1779.topic&index=45><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.threadControl?topicID=1779.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.subscribeUnregi